main event: A civilian reported an unidentified aerial phenomena sighting on June 24, 1967, in Van Nuys, California.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 5-10 minutes and was conducted through ground visual., The specific number of objects observed was insufficient for evaluation., The witness mentioned the object appeared to look like headlights reflecting off a cloud., The object was reported to have disappeared and reappeared during the sighting., The witness, who is male and 29 years old, had a friend with him at the time of the observation.
witness description: male, 29 years old, civilian from Woodland Hills, California
